Free Energy Landscape
---

n_states: 186

Here we see the first two tICs projected, forming a reasonable energy landscape, along with the top few paths. tIC1 seems to correspond to binding(smaller values correspond to bound), while tIC2 reflects some mixture of dihedral/rmsd space. The landscape itself pretty shallow (ignore the labels on the colorbar, as their on a relative scale) and the paths are fairly homogeneousâ€“ apart from path 2, which might be interesting to follow up on.

S100B
===

Free Energy Landscape
---

n_states: 27

n_tICS: 5

Here we see the first two tICs projected, forming a weird-looking landscape upon first glance but it actually pretty elegant (I think...). tIC1 represents binding just as in the plot of Sirtuin, but it seems that tIC2 represents folding. So what we get is this cool 4-state macrostate model for folding-upon binding, and the paths form something resembling a thermodynamic cycle (although unbound,unfolded -> bound,unfolded -> bound,folded is much more represented in the rest of the paths).

Along the Paths
---

Here we see the top two paths, which look pretty different than what's going on in Sir2. Again, there's a 1 kcal difference between source and sinks, but, in path 2, we see that unbound and folded is about as favorable as being bound. This is pretty consistent with the experimental literature I've been reading (e.g. propensity to form an alpha helix), and seems to make sense biologically if we consider that low-affinity binding is what allows this P53 peptide to be such a promiscuous binder.
